Metric
Formula
Clinical Interpretation
Precision
TP / (TP + FP)
Fraction of generated entities that are correct (anti-hallucination measure)
Recall
TP / (TP + FN)
Fraction of gold entities captured in the generated summary (anti-omission measure)
F1 Score
2 × (P × R) / (P + R)
Harmonic mean of precision and recall
Omission Rate
FN / (TP + FN)
Proportion of important clinical entities missed by the model
Hallucination Rate
FP / (TP + FP)
Proportion of generated entities not supported by the gold summary
 
Omission rate and hallucination rate are of particular clinical importance. In a safety-critical clinical summarization system, a high omission rate may result in important diagnoses or treatments being overlooked, while a high hallucination rate could lead to incorrect clinical decisions. These two error types are therefore analyzed separately in addition to the aggregate F1 score.
